    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a challenging slate today, exacerbated by the confirmed rainouts of **Yordan Alvarez**, **Trea Turner**, and **Kyle Schwarber**, which forces us to rely heavily on our depth. Our strongest play of the day is undoubtedly **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (76.26), who benefits from a prime matchup against Waldron and his high 7.83 xERA. Despite the lower batting order spot, the combination of his elite speed\u2014critical for our scarcity-driven strategy\u2014and the massive SP skill bump makes him our must-start anchor. Close behind is **Junior Caminero** (74.22), whose consistent presence in the #2 hole against Williams provides the highest floor on the team today, as he is perfectly positioned to drive in runs and capitalize on volume.\n\nConversely, our lineup composition reflects calculated risks against tough pitching. **Colt Keith** (46.51) barely cleared the threshold for a start, as his matchup against Ritchie (2.57 xERA) significantly depresses his potential; however, his top-of-the-order protection keeps him in the lineup over **Dillon Dingler** (33.15). The decision to bench **Dillon Dingler** was the most straightforward of the day, as he failed to crack our 40.0 efficiency floor; the negative impact of facing Ritchie, combined with a poor dynamic platoon split, made him an easy exclusion. Elsewhere, **Hyeseong Kim** (61.99) remains a high-upside play, bolstered by a +5% wind-out factor that pushes his scoring profile well into the \"Strong\" category, even from the bottom third of the order. With the weather-impacted roster gaps, we are leaning into speed and favorable platoon edges from **Chase Meidroth** and **Gary Sanchez** to mitigate the loss of our middle-of-the-order power hitters.",
